Module com.inventorysystem
Package com.inventorysystem

Class modifyProductFormController

java.lang.Object
com.inventorysystem.modifyProductFormController
All Implemented Interfaces:
javafx.fxml.Initializable
public class modifyProductFormController
extends java.lang.Object
implements javafx.fxml.Initializable
This is the controller for the modifyProduct page. The purpose of this controller is to modify existing products and to add associated parts to the products.
Author:
Carlos Rodriguez

  • Method Details

    • addAssociatedPartBtn

      public void addAssociatedPartBtn()
      This method adds an associated part to the product. Each product has its own associated parts, this adds it to that specific product and displays it to the table. RUNTIME ERROR had trouble adding parts to a product without it applying to all tables, this was fixed when we gave each product its own private array list.

    • removeAssociatedPartBtn

      public void removeAssociatedPartBtn()
      This method deletes an associated part from the product. Each product has its own associated parts, this deletes it from that specific product and displays the new information on the table.

    • initialize

      public void initialize​(java.net.URL url, java.util.ResourceBundle resourceBundle)
      This method sets up the two tables on the modifyProduct page. On initialization the method will set up the Part table and Product table.
      Specified by:
      initialize in interface javafx.fxml.Initializable

    • saveBtn

      public void saveBtn​(javafx.event.ActionEvent e) throws java.io.IOException
      The save button returns you to the main page and adds to the Product table. Once pressed this method will run multiple checks to verify the input before adding to the Product table and then return the user to the main page.
      Throws:
      java.io.IOException

    • switchToMainForm

      public void switchToMainForm​(javafx.event.ActionEvent e) throws java.io.IOException
      The cancel button returns you to the main page. Once pressed the user will return to the main page and not save any new information.
      Throws:
      java.io.IOException

    • searchPartTable

      public void searchPartTable​(javafx.event.ActionEvent e)
      This method regulates how the app searches through the part table. When text is entered in the search bar, the method will run through checks to filter out the table.
